B138 — LEGENDARY HUNTBOUND RELICS (AGI · LV 60)
1. Overview

These are your endgame AGI DPS legendaries:

Skyshatter Huntbow — ranged legendary for bow users.

Nightveil Prowler — melee dagger legendary for stealth/rogue-style builds.

They’re meant to:

Sit about 25–30% stronger than a perfect Lv 60 Rare.

Hook into all previous “hunt” fantasies:

Verdant Shrikewolf, Charhound, Frostmaw Lynx, Moonless Stag, etc.

Reward players who engage with apex hunts and rare beasts across all zones.

2. Skyshatter Huntbow (Legendary Bow)
2.1 Item Definition

Skyshatter Huntbow
Level 60 · Bow · Legendary

Stats:

+48 Agility

+34 Stamina

+110 Ranged Attack Power

+3% Ranged Crit Chance

+1% Hit Chance

Passive — Hunter’s Focus:

Your ranged critical hits grant 1 stack of Hunter’s Focus (up to 5).

At 5 stacks, your next aimed/special shot:

Consumes all stacks.

Deals +30% damage.

Slows the target by 40% for 4 seconds.

Internal cooldown on the empowered shot: 18 seconds.

Passive — Skystrider:

While in combat and not within melee range of any enemy:

Gain +5% movement speed.

Fall damage reduced by 50%.

This gives hunters/ranged AGI a clear “kite god” fantasy.

2.2 Acquisition — The Grand Hunt (Bow Route)

Questline name: “The Grand Hunt: Skyshatter”

Structure:

Hunt the Old Prey (revisits old apex beasts).

Hunt the Broken Skies (special sky/flight encounters).

Hunt the Final Shadow” (instance / scenario).

Step 1 — Hunt the Old Prey

Objectives:

Slay each of these while tagged with a Hunt Sigil:

Verdant Shrikewolf (Greatwood)

Lavaspine Basilisk (Ashen Ridge)

Frostmaw Lynx (Frostmarch)

Moonless Stag (Duskhollow)

Each kill must be:

With the Huntmaster’s Sigil item in your bags (or off-hand cosmetic).

Within a certain time window after “marking” them (prevents cheesing old kills).

Each kill drops a bound quest item:

Shrikewolf Hunt-Trophy

Lavaspine Hunt-Trophy

Frostmaw Hunt-Trophy

Moonless Hunt-Trophy

Turn in all four to Huntmaster Ralden in your hub.

Reward:

“Skyshatter Bowframe” (incomplete legendary base).

Next quest.

Step 2 — Hunt the Broken Skies

Instance / world events focused on moving targets and positional play.

Objectives:

Ashen Ridge — “The Ember Vulture Flight”

Fight a special flock of Pyre Vultures on cliff edges.

You must land killing blows with ranged attacks while avoiding knock-offs.

Frostmarch — “Aurora’s Prey”

During an aurora event, track and kill a unique aurora-phase predator:

The Star-Fanged Vyraxx.

It phases in and out; only visible while under a special “Aurora Sight” buff.

Duskhollow — “Shadow of the Sky”

An aerial-ish shadow beast, Umbral Roc of Duskhollow, swoops in.

You must dodge line attacks and shoot weak points when it dips.

When all three are done, upgrade:

Skyshatter Bowframe → Skyshatter Heartstring Frame

Reward:

Next quest: “Hunt the Final Shadow.”

Step 3 — Hunt the Final Shadow

Instance: “The Shattered Sky Hunt”

Small 3–5 player scenario, or high-end solo challenge.

Boss: The Sky-Eater Shade, a fusion of shadow beast + sky predator.

Mechanics:

Constant movement, void zones, targeted hail, line shots.

Periodically steals your Hunter’s Focus mechanic, forcing timing plays:

You need to break shields by timing your own empowered shot windows.

Success:

Reward: Skyshatter Huntbow (Legendary).

Frame consumed.

2.3 Quest Skeleton (Lua)
Quests["LEGENDARIES.SKYSHATTER_HUNTBOW"] = {
    id = "Q_LEGENDARY_SKYSHATTER",
    name = "The Grand Hunt: Skyshatter",
